  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Scaling up existing gpsa project Improving social accountability in water sector</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2016, the Global Partnership for Social Accountability (GPSA) and the Water Partnership Program (WPP), both programs housed at the World Bank, initiated a collaboration to accelerate and scale up the adoption of social accountability mechanisms in the water sector through knowledge and programmatic activities involving citizens, government, Bank staff, service providers, and relevant stakeholders. As part of this collaboration, the GPSA will work with Oxfam Great Britain (GB) to lead the implementation of programmatic activities to advance the social accountability agenda in the water sector in Tajikistan.   Oxfam GB will be responsible for adapting and mainstreaming social accountability tools developed under the Drinking Water Supply and Sanitation Sector Improving Social Accountability (TWISA) programme in selected micro districts in Khujand; subcontracting and empowering water service providers to adopt performance indicators and disseminate information collected; strengthening capacity and oversight functions of citizens, particularly women; and producing knowledge and learning products.</narrative>
  </description>
